Hm, hum.

Looking at the backtrace again, it appears this is now a duplicate of bug 154735, which is a Platform bug.

The problem (assertion failed... refactoring history) appears only the first time the properties page is shown. On later invocations, the Refactoring History Property Page does not intervene any more.

The culprit of this problem is probably not RSE but the Platform. See bug
154735. Workaround:

* Open the Subsystem Properties Page
* In case a "Refactoring History" page is there, close the Properties dlg
* Open it again; now, you can set the subsystem port

Could somebody please verify this.

Verified with eclipse-platform-I20061121-1845 that this does not happen any more.
The AssertionFailedError was never our problem.

This will finally be fixed with Eclipse-3.3M4 and later.
Until then, all we can do is document it on the known issues and workarounds page.

Marking fixed as per RSE-1.0
